        <div class="msgSubject">New display mode: Windowed (Full-Screen)</div>
        <div class="sm notbold">
          
          Posted: 2010-11-10 14:06:20   | <input type="checkbox" name="quote-128941958030615086" id="quote-128941958030615086" class="msgQuoteCheck" onchange="multiQuote2()"/><label for="quote-128941958030615086" onclick="multiQuote2()"> Quote</label>  | <a href="/forum.html?forum=173&amp;mid=128941958030615086&amp;post=1&amp;replyto=128941958030615086&amp;page=1" class="icon-replytothis" rel="nofollow">Reply to Post</a> | <a id="FOLLOW_MID_128941958030615086" onclick="followToggle('add','128941958030615086')" href="javascript:" class="icon-follow">Follow</a> 
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName " href="/users/Rhianu">Rhianu</a></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/></div><div class="msgWhoNum">297 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Good  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">Right now, in the FFXIV configuration program, there are only two options for display mode: Windowed mode, and Full-Screen mode. Full-Screen mode has the advantage of completely filling your entire screen for the optimum visuals, thus making it easier to immerse yourself in the game's world, while Windowed mode offers the convenience of having a web browser or other program open in the background, allowing players to multitask or look up online guides without leaving the game. <br /> <br />However, there are many people (myself included) who want the best of both worlds. That is, we want the convenience of Windowed mode, but without sacrificing the superior visuals of Full-Screen mode. Personally, I love playing in Full-Screen mode simply because I have OCD and having the window boarders around my game-screen bugs the crap out of me. But being unable to switch to other programs while playing FFXIV is super annoying as well. And from my observations, there are many, many other people who feel the same way. <br /> <br />So I propose a new display mode: Windowed (Full-Screen) mode. This display mode is already in use in many other PC games (such as StarCraft II), and is becoming increasingly common. Basically what it does is reposition and lock the game window so it makes the game LOOK like it's in Full-Screen mode, yet BEHAVE as though it were still in Windowed mode (which it is, technically). <br /> <br />There are programs out there that can force this type of behavior, but I think it would be more user-friendly if SE were to implement it officially. That way people (both players and SE alike) don't have to worry about walking the thin line between harmless modding and blatant hacking (not to mention SE apparently has legal concerns as well, what with that threatening letter they sent to the creator of FFXIV windower). <br /> <br />In the end, I really think that implementing an official Windowed (Full-Screen) mode would be in everybody's best interest. It would give players the functionality they desire, while also covering SE's back, protecting the integrity of both the game and SE as a company (plus it gives the impression that SE actually listens to their player-base). <br /> <br />All in all, adding Windowed (Full-Screen) as a new option for display mode would make FFXIV a much more enjoyable experience all around. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><span class="sm"><i>P.S. If SE could also make it so that regular Full-Screen mode doesn't crash when alt-tabbing to another program, that would be great!</i></span></div>
