      <div class="msgContentFrame">Yeah, seeing a bar is a minor detail, but for some of us, especially people like me that can't ignore little things like that, it ruins the whole experience. ; ; <br /> <br />I wish I was good enough to be able to ignore it, but this is a guy who can recognize sounds coming from the waking world when he's dreaming and decide whether it's worth waking up or ignoring. (unless it's real loud, then it breaks me out of dream mode and I rage at the garbage truck, but that's going off topic) <br /> <br />I realize the dev team is already overworked and freaking out over the sheer amount of fixes and improvements to the game they gotta do already thanks to their impatient bosses, but considering how popular the third party tool windower is for ffxi, it probably would be prudent to make this patch right away, making a full screen windowed mode for those of us who know how to (ab)use alt+tab, since this would be safer than putting countless customers to trusting third party programs and potential security risks to get what should be considered a necessary part of any game.  <br /> <br />Fix it ASAP in my opinion. That way, you save the potential headaches of who knows how many customers using third party programs, because they will, and have less congestion with customer service having to deal with hacked accounts and the like. Heck, if you really are pressed for time, you could just hire/get volunteers to do that for you, and check the code to make sure it's secure. In this day and age with the wonders of firefox, noscript, and open source software, it should be a piece of cake to find people to help you out on this if you don't have the time to fix it yourselves. :3<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Main Character: Psion <br />World: Phoenix <br />Resident of Windurst <br />75BLU/75PUP/70COR <br /><a href="http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?186284" title="http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.x